         <abstract id="aspace_314a87c1f8115eaf375f0dd8157c3fe6">Collection of sixteen inkjet prints that present diptych photographs of places in Miami and South Florida created by Karen Halverson in 2019. The images explore rising sea levels caused by global warming and its expected impact on Miami and South Florida. Each inkjet print presents two photographic images (26 x 39 cm each) comprised of a documentary view of a site in Florida paired with the same image as a composite photograph with an ocean water level applied to the lower portion of it. Identified sites in Miami include the Miami Design District, Port of Miami, and the Vizcaya Museum and Gardens in the Coconut Grove neighborhood. Identified sites in South Florida include Dania Beach, the Seminole Hard Rock Hotel &amp; Casino Hollywood, Key West, Marathon, and Miami Beach.</abstract>
